A 'Rubus idaeus' is a species of deciduous shrub in the rose family. 
Its stems are light brown and covered in prickly thorns. 
The leaves are green and have serrated edges. 
The fruit of the Rubus idaeus is called a raspberry and is typically a bright red color when fully ripe. 
The texture of the fruit is soft and juicy, and it contains small seeds throughout. 
This plant can be found growing in temperate regions around the world, often in fields, forests, and along roadsides. 
'Rubi idaeus' is commonly used for culinary purposes, including making jams, jellies, and desserts.
